I would like to change my review for Benny’s! At first, I did not like this spot so much because I felt that the pizza was a bit overpriced and the cheese one time stuck to the box, but I had a different experience at Benny’s today. I was really hungry & I needed quick food. I went inside & I ordered the grandma sauce low carb pizza. I got to be honest, it was one of the best thin crusts pizzas I’ve ever ate! I really liked the pizza & I like that they allow me to have free toppings!! Pizza professor across the street makes you pay for toppings, but Benny’s really came in CLUTCH today when I was hungry & needed quick food. Plus, it was delicious. I also had the cheese fries a couple months ago, and I loved it. I gave Benny’s 3 stars before.... now I’m giving it 5! I’ll be back for more low carb pizza! :)

I'll start with the important part, they make excellent pizza! I use the single regular slice test at any place I walk into. I order a single slice and eat it. If possible several times over a few days, and I rate the slice. On my scale this one is a 10. The best I ever tasted, although my experience is limited to kosher establishments, I do think I tasted most of those in NYC.  Other types of slices are also excellent, vodka sauce, zette, white, original, deep dish. They also serve excellent battered french fries, onion rings, soups, their Mac & Cheese is also excellent and also more pasta which is prepared on the spot, everything is made fresh. Salad bar is much in demand from what I can see,  However, not everything is awesome, it's not a large place and it is busy, you might need to wait some time for service, it isn't very clean, and ordering is a bit slow - you need to know what you want, you usually won't get much help from the person at the register. But... The food operation itself does look clean, and once ordered the pizza doesn't take long to get to your mouth (beware, boiling hot!)
